# Frontend Conventions

Client-side code runs in the browser. It handles rendering, user interaction, state management, and communication with the backend API routes.

## Architecture Boundary

Frontend code lives in:
- `src/shell/` — AppShell grid layout + ContainerSlot isolation wrappers
- `src/containers/` — Self-contained UI regions (Header, Sidebar, Chat, etc.)
- `src/components/ui/` — Radix-based design system primitives
- `src/app/**/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx` — Next.js pages and layouts

Frontend code must **never**:
- Import from `src/lib/tools/` or `src/lib/prompts/` (server-only modules)
- Use Node.js APIs (`fs`, `path`, `child_process`, `process.env` for secrets)
- Access the AI SDK's server functions (`streamText`, `tool`) — use `useChat` from `@ai-sdk/react` instead
- Read environment variables directly — secrets stay server-side, exposed only through API routes

## Client Directive

Any component that uses hooks, event handlers, browser APIs, or Zustand must declare `"use client"` as the first line. Components that are purely presentational and data-fetched via server components should omit it.

```typescript
// Needs "use client" — has hooks and interactivity
"use client";

import { useState } from "react";
export function Counter() { ... }

// No directive needed — server component rendering static content
export function StaticBanner() {
  return <div>Welcome</div>;
}
```

## Component Patterns

### Container Components (`src/containers/`)

Containers are the primary UI building blocks. Each one:
- Lives in its own directory: `src/containers/<Name>/<Name>.tsx`
- Has a typed props interface (even if empty)
- Is wrapped by `ContainerSlot` (ErrorBoundary + Suspense) in `AppShell`
- Cleans up all effects on unmount (containers can be remounted via key changes)

```typescript
"use client";

interface HeaderProps {}

export function Header({}: HeaderProps) {
  // all hooks, state, effects here
  return ( ... );
}
```

### UI Primitives (`src/components/ui/`)

Primitives wrap Radix UI and are styled with Tailwind:
- Always use `forwardRef` and spread `...props`
- Merge classNames via `cn()` — never replace consumer classes
- Use `cva` for variant typing
- Zero business logic — purely presentational

## State Management

### Zustand for Persistent State

State that must survive container remounts (key-based reload, HMR) uses Zustand stores at module scope:

```typescript
import { create } from "zustand";

interface ChatState {
  isOpen: boolean;
  toggleOpen: () => void;
  setOpen: (open: boolean) => void;
}

export const useChatStore = create<ChatState>((set) => ({
  isOpen: false,
  toggleOpen: () => set((s) => ({ isOpen: !s.isOpen })),
  setOpen: (open) => set({ isOpen: open }),
}));
```

- Always use selectors: `useChatStore((s) => s.isOpen)` — never `useChatStore()`
- Store interfaces must be explicit — no `any`, no untyped `set`

### React State for Ephemeral UI

Use `useState` / `useReducer` for state that should reset on remount (form inputs, scroll position, local toggles).

## AI Integration (Client Side)

The only client-side AI hook is `useChat` from `@ai-sdk/react`:

```typescript
import { useChat } from "@ai-sdk/react";
import { DefaultChatTransport } from "ai";

const { messages, sendMessage, status, error } = useChat({
  transport: new DefaultChatTransport({ api: "/api/chat" }),
});
```

### Rules

- `useChat` lives exclusively in the Chat container — no other container calls the AI API
- The `api` endpoint must match the backend route (`/api/chat`)
- Check `status` for loading states: `"streaming" | "submitted"` means loading
- Never pass API keys or model config on the client — all configuration lives server-side

## Styling

- All styling through Tailwind utility classes — no inline `style` objects except for dynamic values the design system can't express
- Use CSS custom properties (`var(--font-geist-sans)`) for font families
- Use OKLCH color tokens defined in `globals.css` — never hard-code hex/rgb
- Animations use Framer Motion (`motion.div`) with spring physics — keep transitions under 300ms
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for non-essential animations

## Accessibility

- Interactive `<div>` elements must have `role="button"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and keyboard handlers
- All icon-only buttons need `aria-label`
- Form inputs need associated labels
- Focus states must be visible — never remove outlines without replacement
